# Story 7.1: Scenario Sandbox Mode

## Story Metadata
- **Epic:** 7 - What-If Scenario Planning System
- **Story ID:** 7-1-scenario-sandbox-mode
- **Status:** ready-for-dev
- **Priority:** P0
- **Persona:** Paul (Fleet Planner)
- **Added:** SCP-001 (2025-12-28)

## User Story
As a **Fleet Planner**,
I want **to create a sandbox copy of current fleet state**,
So that **I can experiment with changes without affecting live data**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status | Visual Verification |
|----|----------|--------|---------------------|
| AC1 | "Create Scenario" button visible and functional | PENDING | Playwright screenshot required |
| AC2 | Button clones current allocation state | PENDING | |
| AC3 | Sandbox visually distinguished (badge/border) | PENDING | |
| AC4 | Changes in sandbox don't affect live data | PENDING | |
| AC5 | Can discard sandbox anytime | PENDING | |

## Technical Requirements

### API Endpoints
```typescript
// Create new scenario sandbox
POST /api/scenarios
Request: { name: string }
Response: {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  createdAt: Date;
  status: 'draft';
  snapshot: AllocationSnapshot;
}

// List scenarios
GET /api/scenarios
Response: Scenario[]

// Delete scenario
DELETE /api/scenarios/:id
Response: { success: boolean }
```

### State Management
```typescript
interface ScenarioState {
  isActive: boolean;
  activeScenarioId: string | null;
  scenarios: Scenario[];
}

interface Scenario {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  createdAt: Date;
  status: 'draft' | 'simulated' | 'applied';
  baselineSnapshot: {
    allocations: Allocation[];
    trainStates: TrainState[];
    timestamp: Date;
  };
  modifications: Modification[];
}
```

### UI Components
1. **ScenarioToolbar** - Shows current mode, scenario name
2. **CreateScenarioDialog** - Name input, create button
3. **ScenarioIndicator** - Visual badge when in sandbox mode
4. **DiscardButton** - Exit sandbox with confirmation

### Visual Design
```css
/* Sandbox mode indicator */
.sandbox-mode {
  border: 2px solid #F59E0B; /* amber-500 */
  box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.3);
}

.sandbox-badge {
  background: #F59E0B;
  color: #000;
  padding: 2px 8px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-size: 12px;
}
```

## Implementation Notes
- Sandbox must be clearly visible - users must know they're in scenario mode
- Clone should be deep copy to ensure isolation
- Discard must have confirmation to prevent accidental data loss
- Foundation for Stories 7.2 through 7.6

## Test Scenarios
1. Create scenario → verify sandbox indicator appears
2. Make changes in sandbox → verify live data unchanged
3. Discard scenario → verify return to live mode
4. Create multiple scenarios → verify list works

## Dependencies
- Epic 1 (API foundation)
- Epic 5 (Balancing foundation)

## Playwright Visual Tests Required
- [ ] Screenshot: Create Scenario button visible
- [ ] Screenshot: Sandbox mode indicator active
- [ ] Screenshot: Scenario list populated
- [ ] Screenshot: Discard confirmation dialog

# Story 7.3: Workforce/Vacation Planning

## Story Metadata
- **Epic:** 7 - What-If Scenario Planning System
- **Story ID:** 7-3-workforce-vacation-planning
- **Status:** backlog
- **Priority:** P1
- **Persona:** Maria (Maintenance Manager)
- **Added:** SCP-001 (2025-12-28)

## User Story
As a **Maintenance Manager**,
I want **to simulate staff absences**,
So that **I can test coverage during holidays**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status | Visual Verification |
|----|----------|--------|---------------------|
| AC1 | Can mark dates as reduced capacity | PENDING | Playwright screenshot required |
| AC2 | Depot capacity reflects reductions | PENDING | |
| AC3 | Conflict warnings if over-scheduled | PENDING | |
| AC4 | Calendar visualization shows absences | PENDING | |
| AC5 | Can specify reduction percentage | PENDING | |

## Technical Requirements

### API Endpoints
```typescript
// Add capacity reduction
POST /api/scenarios/:id/capacity-reductions
Request: {
  depotId: string;
  startDate: Date;
  endDate: Date;
  reductionPercent: number; // 0-100
  reason: string;           // e.g., "Summer vacation"
}
Response: { reduction: CapacityReduction; conflicts: Conflict[] }

// List reductions
GET /api/scenarios/:id/capacity-reductions
Response: CapacityReduction[]

// Remove reduction
DELETE /api/scenarios/:id/capacity-reductions/:id
Response: { success: boolean }
```

### Data Model
```typescript
interface CapacityReduction {
  id: string;
  scenarioId: string;
  depotId: string;
  startDate: Date;
  endDate: Date;
  reductionPercent: number;
  reason: string;
  conflicts: Conflict[];
}

interface Conflict {
  type: 'overbooked';
  date: Date;
  depotId: string;
  scheduledMaintenance: number;
  availableCapacity: number;
}
```

### UI Components
1. **CapacityCalendar** - Visual calendar with reduction overlays
2. **AddReductionDialog** - Form for new reduction
3. **ConflictWarnings** - Alert panel for over-scheduled periods
4. **DepotCapacityChart** - Shows reduced capacity

### Calendar View
- Color-coded days showing capacity levels
- Red overlay for reduced capacity periods
- Hover shows details (reason, percentage)

## Implementation Notes
- Common use case: holiday periods, summer vacations
- Conflicts should prevent Apply-to-Live without resolution
- Multiple reductions can overlap (stack percentages)
- Depends on Story 7.1 (sandbox mode)

## Dependencies
- Story 7.1 (scenario sandbox)
- Epic 6 (depot capacity foundation)

## Playwright Visual Tests Required
- [ ] Screenshot: Capacity calendar with reduction
- [ ] Screenshot: Add reduction dialog
- [ ] Screenshot: Conflict warning displayed
- [ ] Screenshot: Depot capacity chart with reduction

# Story 7.4: Budget Allocation Scenarios

## Story Metadata
- **Epic:** 7 - What-If Scenario Planning System
- **Story ID:** 7-4-budget-allocation-scenarios
- **Status:** backlog
- **Priority:** P2
- **Persona:** Gabriel (Fleet Manager)
- **Added:** SCP-001 (2025-12-28)

## User Story
As a **Fleet Manager**,
I want **to test different budget distributions**,
So that **I can optimize maintenance spending**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status | Visual Verification |
|----|----------|--------|---------------------|
| AC1 | Can set budget per depot/period | PENDING | Playwright screenshot required |
| AC2 | Shows maintenance coverage at budget | PENDING | |
| AC3 | Highlights unfunded maintenance | PENDING | |
| AC4 | ROI estimates displayed | PENDING | |
| AC5 | Can compare budget distributions | PENDING | |

## Technical Requirements

### API Endpoints
```typescript
// Set budget allocation
PUT /api/scenarios/:id/budget
Request: {
  totalBudget: number;
  allocations: Array<{
    depotId: string;
    periodStart: Date;
    periodEnd: Date;
    amount: number;
  }>;
}
Response: {
  budget: BudgetAllocation;
  coverage: CoverageAnalysis;
}

// Get coverage analysis
GET /api/scenarios/:id/budget/coverage
Response: CoverageAnalysis
```

### Data Model
```typescript
interface BudgetAllocation {
  scenarioId: string;
  totalBudget: number;
  allocations: DepotBudget[];
}

interface DepotBudget {
  depotId: string;
  periodStart: Date;
  periodEnd: Date;
  amount: number;
  maintenanceCost: number;
  coverage: number; // 0-100%
}

interface CoverageAnalysis {
  totalMaintenance: number;
  fundedMaintenance: number;
  unfundedMaintenance: MaintenanceEvent[];
  coveragePercent: number;
  estimatedRoi: number;
}
```

### UI Components
1. **BudgetEditor** - Allocation sliders/inputs per depot
2. **CoverageChart** - Visual coverage by depot
3. **UnfundedList** - List of maintenance at risk
4. **RoiDisplay** - Estimated return on maintenance spend

### Cost Model
```typescript
const maintenanceCosts = {
  PM1: 5000,   // EUR
  PM2: 15000,  // EUR
  HM: 50000,   // EUR
  OVH: 200000, // EUR
};
```

## Implementation Notes
- Budget planning is lower priority (P2) but adds demo value
- ROI calculation based on avoided breakdown costs
- Unfunded maintenance creates risk that should be visible
- Depends on Story 7.1 (sandbox mode)

## Dependencies
- Story 7.1 (scenario sandbox)
- Epic 6 (maintenance schedule)

## Playwright Visual Tests Required
- [ ] Screenshot: Budget editor interface
- [ ] Screenshot: Coverage chart by depot
- [ ] Screenshot: Unfunded maintenance list
- [ ] Screenshot: ROI estimate display

# Story 7.6: Apply Scenario to Live

## Story Metadata
- **Epic:** 7 - What-If Scenario Planning System
- **Story ID:** 7-6-apply-scenario-to-live
- **Status:** backlog
- **Priority:** P1
- **Persona:** Gabriel (Fleet Manager)
- **Added:** SCP-001 (2025-12-28)

## User Story
As a **Fleet Manager**,
I want **to commit an approved scenario**,
So that **changes become the new baseline**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status | Visual Verification |
|----|----------|--------|---------------------|
| AC1 | "Apply to Live" button with confirmation | PENDING | Playwright screenshot required |
| AC2 | Summary of changes shown before apply | PENDING | |
| AC3 | Audit trail of changes created | PENDING | |
| AC4 | Rollback capability within 24h | PENDING | |
| AC5 | Notification to stakeholders | PENDING | |

## Technical Requirements

### API Endpoints
```typescript
// Preview changes before apply
GET /api/scenarios/:id/preview-apply
Response: {
  changes: Change[];
  affectedTrains: number;
  affectedServices: number;
  warnings: string[];
}

// Apply scenario to production
POST /api/scenarios/:id/apply
Request: {
  confirmationCode: string;  // User must type "APPLY"
  notifyStakeholders: boolean;
}
Response: {
  success: boolean;
  appliedAt: Date;
  rollbackToken: string;  // Valid for 24h
  auditLogId: string;
}

// Rollback applied scenario
POST /api/scenarios/:id/rollback
Request: { rollbackToken: string }
Response: { success: boolean; restoredState: Date }
```

### Data Model
```typescript
interface AuditLog {
  id: string;
  scenarioId: string;
  appliedAt: Date;
  appliedBy: string;
  changes: Change[];
  rollbackToken: string;
  rollbackExpiry: Date;
  rolledBack: boolean;
}

interface Change {
  type: 'allocation' | 'train_added' | 'train_removed' | 'capacity' | 'budget';
  before: any;
  after: any;
  description: string;
}
```

### UI Components
1. **ApplyButton** - With confirmation state
2. **ChangeSummaryDialog** - Shows all changes before apply
3. **ConfirmationInput** - Type "APPLY" to confirm
4. **RollbackPanel** - Shows in 24h window after apply
5. **NotificationToggle** - Option to notify stakeholders

### Safety Measures
- Requires typing "APPLY" to confirm
- Shows warning for high-impact changes
- 24h rollback window
- Audit trail for compliance

## Implementation Notes
- This is a destructive action - maximum safety required
- Preview must show ALL changes clearly
- Rollback is critical for user confidence
- Notification system optional but valuable

## Dependencies
- Story 7.1 (scenario creation)
- Story 7.5 (comparison - user picks which to apply)

## Playwright Visual Tests Required
- [ ] Screenshot: Apply button visible
- [ ] Screenshot: Change summary dialog
- [ ] Screenshot: Confirmation input ("APPLY")
- [ ] Screenshot: Rollback panel after apply

